<subSubSection id="C3046574821F136F25A581F1FBE8FA07" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA136FF821F136F25A581F1FAE8FAEA" blockId="60.[151,1436,1266,1471]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED821F136F25A581F1FEA3FA97" bold="true" box="[151,273,1266,1291]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Lacking intermarginal denticles in chelicerae (
<figureCitation id="13252A7A821F136F267681F1FC1FFA96" box="[836,941,1266,1290]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1822,1845]" captionTargetBox="[186,1401,206,1788]" captionTargetId="figure-54@61.[151,1436,193,1801]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 37. Eusparassus tuckeri (Lawrence, 1927) comb. nov., holotype male from Namibia: Kunene Riverside (SAMC). (a) left palp, ventral; (b) left palp, retrolateral; (c) embolus tip and conductor, ventral; (d) eye arrangement, dorsal; (e) right chelicera, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422691" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422691/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Figs 37e</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13252A7A821F136F268D81F1FC59FA96" box="[959,1003,1266,1290]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1715,1738]" captionTargetBox="[151,1411,193,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-146@66.[151,1436,193,1694]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 40. Eusparassus educatus spec. nov., holotype male from Namibia: NE of Juriesdraai (SMF). (a) left palp, ventral; (b) left palp, retrolateral; (c) embolus tip and conductor, ventral; (d) eye arrangement, dorsal; (e) right chelicera, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422699/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">40e</figureCitation>
); female epigyne with AMLL fused together and encircling MS entirely (
<figureCitation id="13252A7A821F136F27008015FD27FAB2" box="[562,661,1302,1326]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="62.[151,250,1809,1832]" captionTargetBox="[154,1435,209,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-54@62.[151,1436,200,1763]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 38. Eusparassus tuckeri (Lawrence, 1927) comb. nov., female from Namibia: Kunene Riverside [lectotype female of “Olios furcatus” (SAMC)]. (a) epigyne, ventral; (b) vulva, dorsal; (c) left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422695/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Figs 38a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13252A7A821F136F27938015FD7FFAB2" box="[673,717,1302,1326]" captionStart="FIGURE 41" captionStartId="67.[151,250,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[158,1426,205,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-81@67.[151,1436,193,1842]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURE 41. Eusparassus educatus spec. nov., (a–c) paratypes from Namibia: Epupa Falls (SMF). (a) epigyne, ventral; (b) vulva, dorsal; (c) left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral; (d) male’s bulbus with separated embolus from embolic membrane, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422701/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">41a</figureCitation>
); male palps with an enlarged sub-tegulum (not as large as those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C821F136F25848038FEB7FACE" authorityName="Moradmand" authorityYear="2013" box="[182,261,1339,1362]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaegeri">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED821F136F25848038FEB7FACE" box="[182,261,1339,1362]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">jaegeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group) and very long embolus tip, embolus much longer relative to tegulum compared to other species groups; EM developed and forming a process covering ET partially (
<figureCitation id="13252A7A821F136F26A8805DFBA5FAEA" box="[922,1047,1374,1398]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1822,1845]" captionTargetBox="[186,1401,206,1788]" captionTargetId="figure-54@61.[151,1436,193,1801]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 37. Eusparassus tuckeri (Lawrence, 1927) comb. nov., holotype male from Namibia: Kunene Riverside (SAMC). (a) left palp, ventral; (b) left palp, retrolateral; (c) embolus tip and conductor, ventral; (d) eye arrangement, dorsal; (e) right chelicera, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422691" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422691/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Figs 37a–c</figureCitation>
) to completely (
<figureCitation id="13252A7A821F136F21FC805DFAFCFAEA" box="[1230,1358,1374,1398]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1715,1738]" captionTargetBox="[151,1411,193,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-146@66.[151,1436,193,1694]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 40. Eusparassus educatus spec. nov., holotype male from Namibia: NE of Juriesdraai (SMF). (a) left palp, ventral; (b) left palp, retrolateral; (c) embolus tip and conductor, ventral; (d) eye arrangement, dorsal; (e) right chelicera, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6422699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6422699/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Figs 40a–c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136FF821F136F25F58081FBE8FA07" blockId="60.[151,1436,1266,1471]" box="[199,1114,1410,1435]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED821F136F25F58081FE0FFA07" bold="true" box="[199,445,1410,1435]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Species composition.</emphasis>
Two species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C821F136F276E8080FD7BFA07" authorityName="Moradmand" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Lawrence" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[604,713,1411,1435]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuckeri" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED821F136F276E8080FD7BFA07" box="[604,713,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">E. tuckeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96AEAED821F136F27FD8080FCE2FA07" bold="true" box="[719,848,1411,1435]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2595796821F136F27FD8080FCE2FA07" box="[719,848,1411,1435]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C821F136F266C8080FC52FA07" authority="Moradmand, 2013" authorityName="Moradmand" authorityYear="2013" box="[862,992,1411,1435]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="educatus" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED821F136F266C8080FC52FA07" box="[862,992,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">E. educatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96AEAED821F136F26D58080FBE8FA07" bold="true" box="[999,1114,1411,1435]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2595796821F136F26D58080FBE8FA07" box="[999,1114,1411,1435]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
